<vulnerability_guide>
  <title>ML MODEL EXTRACTION AND STEALING</title>

  <critical>Model extraction attacks steal proprietary machine learning models by querying the API and reconstructing a functionally equivalent copy. This threatens intellectual property, enables white-box attacks against the copy, and can expose training data characteristics. A model worth millions can be extracted with thousands of API queries.</critical>

  <scope>
    - Model architecture extraction
    - Weight and parameter theft
    - Training data inference
    - Decision boundary mapping
    - Hyperparameter discovery
    - Functionality replication
  </scope>

