    - Track query diversity and coverage
    - Rate limit sensitive endpoints
    - Watermark model outputs
  </detection>

  <validation>
    - Successfully extract model behavior
    - Achieve high fidelity substitute
    - Demonstrate adversarial transferability
    - Quantify extraction efficiency
    - Document information leakage
  </validation>

  <pro_tips>
    - Confidence scores leak more than labels alone
    - Start with public models matching target domain
    - Active learning dramatically reduces query count
    - Embeddings APIs are direct model theft opportunities
    - LLMs memorize training data - prompt them to reproduce it
    - Query patterns often detected - randomize timing
  </pro_tips>

  <remember>Any model accessible via API can potentially be stolen. The question is cost: how many queries and how much money to reproduce the functionality? If the model returns confidence scores or embeddings, extraction is much easier. Model extraction enables all white-box attacks against the stolen copy, making it a gateway to adversarial attacks, training data extraction, and IP theft.</remember>
